dc_title_s: South Atlantic Ocean, Argentina, Faro Punta Norte to Faro San José (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: prepared and published by the National Imagery and Mapping Agency. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. "From an Argentine chart of 1983." "Reprinted by NIMA 11-97." "Copyright 1997 by the United States Government. No copyright claimed under Title 17 U.S.C." "Soundings in meters." Inset: Isla Escondida. Scale 1:40,000. Includes tidal information in inset. Map No. 23023.Historic paper maps can provide an excellent view of the changes that have occurred in the cultural and physical landscape. The wide range of information provided on these maps make them useful in the study of historic geography, and urban and rural land use change. As this map has been georeferenced, it can be used in a GIS as a source or background layer in conjunction with other GIS data.
dc_creator_sm: United States. National Imagery and Mapping Agency
